
[1]matrimony

   MAT'RIMONY, n. [L. matrimonium, from mater, mother.]

   Marriage; wedlock; the union of man and woman for life; the nuptial
   state.

   If any man know cause why this couple should not be joined in holy
   matrimony, they are to declare it.
